        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 1:01PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 101 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Acoma Pueblo, or 24 miles south of Grants, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Acoma Pueblo, Skyline-Ganipa, McCartys, San Fidel, Acomita Lake,
Acomita, North Acomita Village, Seama and Paraje.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 89 and 100.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
